snippet.textDisplay:
Old people were upset here in Canada that Anne with an E fid not follow the plot of Anne of Green Gables on which it was based.

Anne of Green Gables is a Canadian literary treasure that was very progressive for it's time and people a lot of people are fiercly protective of it as a piece of Canadian history.

What I think they fail to grasp is that "progressive for it's time" does not have the same affect now as it did then. If Anne of Green Gables caused people to rethink social issues back then and does not now then the story is bot fulfilling it's original purpose. As such the team for Anne with an E wanted to update the story for a modern audience so it would be as much of a conversation starter as it used to be.

This resonated with younger audiences here for obvious reasons but also because Anne of Green Gables has been adapted nore than any other Canadian literary piece rather accurately multiple times so this was a frsh take they could go to with the original version always their to return if they wanted a classical or nostalgia factor as well.

But c'est la vie. Some people just want you to adapt the same story the same way over and over and over again.
